## AI Fix Instructions

1. Read each `.log` file in `.github/logs/errors/`.
2. Identify the root cause from the error output.
3. Apply the fix to the relevant source file.
4. Push — CI will re-run, clear the folder, and only write new failures.

### Common Fix Patterns

| Failure Type | Typical Fix |
|-------------|-------------|
| `go vet` | Fix the reported code issue (unused vars, wrong types, etc.) |
| `golangci-lint` | Fix the linting violation or add a `//nolint` comment with justification |
| `govulncheck` (3rd-party) | Run `go get <package>@latest && go mod tidy` |
| `govulncheck` (stdlib) | Upgrade Go version in `go.mod` or wait for patch |
| Test failure | Read the FAIL output, fix the logic or update the test assertion |
| Build failure | Fix compilation errors shown in the build output |
